short_desc: FRMDATEB1L must not be from date before form was released
full_desc: Q0a. FRMDATEB1L (B1L form date) must not be from date before form was released (2017)

test_name: LBSAGERM compared to LBCAREM on D1L
short_desc: If LBSAGERM is not in (888, 999) then Form D1L LBCAREM should not equal 0
full_desc: If Q28. LBSAGERM (Age of onset of probable REM sleep behavior disorder) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown), then Form D1L Q4a. LBCAREM (REM sleep behavior disorder) should not equal 0 (Absent)
test_logic: If LBSAGERM is in (888,999) and LBCAREM=0

test_name: LBSAGERM compared to LBCAREM on D1L
short_desc: If LBSAGERM =888 then Form D1L LBCAREM should not equal 1 or 2
full_desc: If Q28. LBSAGERM (Age of onset of probable REM sleep behavior disorder) is not applicable (888) then Form D1L Q4a. LBCAREM (REM sleep behavior disorder) should not equal 1 or 2 (Questionably or definitely present)

test_name: LBSAGEFL compared to LBCAFALL on D1L

full_desc: If Q31. LBSAGEFL (Age of onset of falls) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown), then Form D1L Q4j. LBCAFALL (Falls) should not equal 0 (Absent)

full_desc: If Q31. LBSAGEFL (Age of onset of falls) is not applicable (888) then Form D1L Q4j. LBCAFALL (Falls) should not equal 1 or 2 (Questionably or definitely present)

test_name: LBSAGETR compared to LBCMRTRM and LBCMATRM on D1L
short_desc: If LBSAGETR is not in (888, 999) then one of Form D1L LBCMRTRM or LBCMATRM should not equal 0
full_desc: If Q32. LBSAGETR (Age of onset of tremor) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown), then one of Form D1L Q2c. LBCMRTRM (Rest tremor) or Q2e. LBCMATRM (Action tremor) should not equal 0
test_logic: If LBSAGETR is in (888,999) and LBCMRTRM=0 and LBCMATRM=0

test_name: LBSAGETR compared to LBCMRTRM and LBCMATRM on D1L
short_desc: If LBSAGETR =888 then both Form D1L LBCMRTRM and LBCMATRM should not equal 1 or 2
full_desc: If Q32. LBSAGETR (Age of onset of tremor) is not applicable (888) then both Form D1L Q2c. LBCMRTRM (Rest tremor) and Q2e. LBCMATRM (Action tremor) should not equal 1 or 2
test_logic: If LBSAGETR =888 and LBCMRTRM in (1,2) and LBCMATRM in (1,2)

full_desc: If Q33. LBSAGEBR (Age of onset of bradykinesia) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown), then Form D1L Q2a. LBCMBRAD (Bradykinesia) should not equal 0 (Absent)
test_logic: If LBSAGEBR is in (888,999) and LBCMBRAD=0

test_name: LBSAGERM compared to BEREMAGO on UDS Form B9 at the same visit
short_desc: If LBSAGERM is not in (888, 999) and UDS Form B9 BEREMAGO is non-missing (9-110), then LBSAGERM should equal BEREMAGO or 777
full_desc: If Q28. LBSAGERM (Age of onset of probable REM sleep behavior disorder) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown) and UDS Form B9 Q12t1. BEREMAGO (Age that REM sleep behavior disorder began) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown), then Q28. LBSAGERM (Age of onset of probable REM sleep behavior disorder) should equal UDS Form B9 Q12t1. BEREMAGO (Age that REM sleep behavior disorder began)
test_logic: If (LBSAGERM is in (888,999) and BEREMAGO is  in (888,999)) and LBSAGERM ne BEREMAGO

test_name: LBSAGEGT compared to GAIT on UDS Form B3 and MOGAIT on UDS Form B9 at the same visit
short_desc: If LBSAGEGT is not in (888, 999) then UDS Form B3 GAIT and UDS Form B9 MOGAIT should not equal 0
full_desc: If Q30. LBSAGEGT (Age of onset of gait disorder) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown), then UDS Form B3 12. GAIT (Gait) and UDS Form B9 Q15a. MOGAIT (Gait problems) should not equal 0 (Gait disorder absent)
test_logic: If LBSAGEGT is in (888,999) and GAIT=0 or MOGAIT=0

test_name: LBSAGEFL compared to MOFALLS on UDS Form B9 at the same visit
short_desc: If LBSAGEFL is not in (888, 999) then UDS Form B9 MOFALLS should not be equal to 0
full_desc: If Q31. LBSAGEFL (Age of onset of falls) is not in (888, 999) (Not applicable or Unknown), then UDS Form B9 Q15b. MOFALLS (Falls) should not be equal to 0
test_logic: If LBSAGEFL is in (888,999) and MOFALLS=0
